- **Omri Tal**: Practiced piano at Jazz Up for 3 weeks now, daily, on my Samui stay. They have two very fine upright acoustic pianos, each in a separate room. The owner is very approachable and welcoming. I highly recommend it for any amateur or professional pianist looking for a practice studio while on the island!
- **Bonnie Maclean**: My son has been doing drum lessons with Jazz Up for over a year now. He loves it and his teacher is amazing. All the teachers here are dedicated musicians and they seem to produce great little music makers! I would definitely recommend this school for anyone looking.
- **JJ K**: Such a great place!!! Teachers are very kind, smiling and always creating warming sweet atmosphere for learning! Great prices and easy to learn. I never knew anything about music and during first lesson already started to play. After 2d lesson I already could play very small part of 15 different songs. If you dream all your life to try musical instruments like me but never have time give it a try and you will discover completely new world for yourself! Definitely Best School on the island!
- **Goya ahmaidia**: I’ve been taking piano lessons at this school for almost a month now, and it’s been a fantastic experience. The teachers are highly dedicated and tailor each lesson to your skill level while continuously helping you improve. They are not only excellent musicians but also truly great educators.
- **Only at Noon**: I''ve had wonderful piano lessons here. The teachers are talented, friendly and warm and they really tailor the lessons to my needs. The atmosphere is welcoming and I’ve made great progress. I highly recommend this school for anyone wanting to learn music—not only do they offer piano lessons, but there’s a lot more available for children, whom I see enjoying their time here, as well as adults like myself!

